cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a method for learning disentangled sets of vector representations of texts that capture distinct aspects, which is a common problem in natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also focuses on a specific application in the biomedical domain, which suggests that it may fall under the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of an adversarial objective and experiments on multi-aspect review corpora suggest that it may also be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The aspect-specific retrieval aspect of the paper may also make it relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of biomedical abstracts suggests that it may be relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category, which deals with the intersection of computing and societal issues.
